#. <section class="sutta" id="sn21.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga"
msgstr "1. Monks"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn21.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Nandasutta"
msgstr "8. With Nanda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.281"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

# This is perhaps the clearest mention of northern black polished ware in the suttas. https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/nanda-and-northern-black-polished-ware/2919
msgctxt "sn21.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā nando bhagavato mātucchāputto ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni "
"pārupitvā akkhīni añjetvā acchaṃ pattaṃ gahetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ "
"kho āyasmantaṃ nandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Nanda—the Buddha’s cousin on his mother’s side—dressed in "
"nicely pressed and ironed robes, applied eyeshadow, and took a polished "
"black bowl. He went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The "
"Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.3"
msgid ""
"“na kho te taṃ, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ ākoṭitapaccākoṭitāni cīvarāni pārupeyyāsi, akkhīni ca "
"añjeyyāsi, acchañca pattaṃ dhāreyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Nanda, as a son of a good family who has gone forth in faith from the lay "
"life to homelessness, it’s not appropriate for you to dress in nicely "
"pressed and ironed robes, apply eyeshadow, and carry a polished black bowl."

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.4"
msgid ""
"Etaṃ kho te, nanda, patirūpaṃ kulaputtassa saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajitassa, yaṃ tvaṃ āraññiko ca assasi, piṇḍapātiko ca paṃsukūliko ca "
"kāmesu ca anapekkho vihareyyāsī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s appropriate for you to stay in the wilderness, eat only alms-food, wear "
"rag robes, and live without concern for sensual pleasures.”"

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn21.8:1.6"
msgid "satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.1"
msgid "“Kadāhaṃ nandaṃ passeyyaṃ,"
msgstr "“When will I see Nanda"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.2"
msgid "āraññaṃ paṃsukūlikaṃ;"
msgstr "in the wilderness, wearing rag robes,"

# uncha = ounce!
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.3"
msgid "Aññātuñchena yāpentaṃ,"
msgstr "feeding on scraps offered by strangers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.8:2.4"
msgid "kāmesu anapekkhinan”ti."
msgstr "unconcerned for sensual pleasures?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.8:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā nando aparena samayena āraññiko ca piṇḍapātiko ca "
"paṃsukūliko ca kāmesu ca anapekkho vihāsīti."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later Venerable Nanda stayed in the wilderness, ate only alms-"
"food, wore rag robes, and lived without concern for sensual pleasures."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.8:3.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
